ABUJA – The Nigerian Upstream Petroleum Regulatory Commission (NUPRC) is set to host all eligible awardees who have fully or partly complied with signature bonus payment in the 2020 marginal field programme (MFBR) at a forum slated for Thursday, 27th January 2022 at the Transcorp Hilton Abuja. In a statement, Engr. Gbenga Komolafe, fnse, the Commission’s Chief Executive, explained that the objective of the engagement forum is to state the policy position of the commission for the marginal field bid round to enable progress of the exercise in line with the programme guidelines and in compliance with the Petroleum Industry Act (PIA) 2021. According to him, the forum will also appraise, distill and clarify issues associated with the MFBR and provide relevant updates on status to all stakeholders in line with transparency policy of government. Buhari Has Extended Fuel Subsidy Removal For Another 18 Months… Fuel Subsidy Removal: TUC Sets Agenda For FG He said that all eligible awardees and relevant international oil companies (IOC) who are associated with the MFBR as farmors are expected to attend the meeting.